{"metadata": {"team_id": "encourage", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1010", "run_id": "encourage-crop"}, "responses": [{"text": "A Saharan dust storm will bring hot, dry weather to San Antonio, TX, with lower rain chances and higher temperatures.", "citations": {"121e372a-9dcd-4b4a-8dd2-1dea85b3c174_804983030": 1.0}}, {"text": "The dust storm will bring hazy sunrises and sunsets, with a 10% chance of rain.", "citations": {"121e372a-9dcd-4b4a-8dd2-1dea85b3c174_804983030": 1.0}}, {"text": "Saharan dust in San Antonio will quiet the tropics and hurricane season for five to seven days.", "citations": {"121e372a-9dcd-4b4a-8dd2-1dea85b3c174_804983030": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Saharan dust storm will bring decreased rainfall and high temperatures to the Americas.", "citations": {"135649f4-82c4-4bc9-903a-9d935421ea27_1026921352": 1.0}}, {"text": "The dust storm will contain iron, silica, fungi, and bacteria, causing respiratory diseases and allergies.", "citations": {"135649f4-82c4-4bc9-903a-9d935421ea27_1026921352": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Saharan dust will affect coral reefs, crops, and raise San Antonio temperatures to the mid-nineties.", "citations": {"135649f4-82c4-4bc9-903a-9d935421ea27_1026921352": 1.0}}, {"text": "The dust storm will originate from Sahara desert storms and move over the Atlantic Ocean and Caribbean Sea with trade winds.", "citations": {"135649f4-82c4-4bc9-903a-9d935421ea27_1026921352": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Saharan dust storm can affect Gulf of Mexico weather and cause skin problems.", "citations": {"135649f4-82c4-4bc9-903a-9d935421ea27_1026921352": 1.0}}, {"text": "Sub-Saharan Africa is the main contributor to Earth's dust storms that reach the Americas.", "citations": {"1fd604e6-30ba-4b91-b53c-ecb5241f2624_55169144": 1.0}}, {"text": "Dust storms occur in spring and autumn due to desertification from low rainfall.", "citations": {"1fd604e6-30ba-4b91-b53c-ecb5241f2624_55169144": 1.0}}, {"text": "Human activities like overgrazing can cause desertification, affecting agriculture and infrastructure.", "citations": {"1fd604e6-30ba-4b91-b53c-ecb5241f2624_55169144": 1.0}}, {"text": "Saharan dust crosses the Atlantic annually from late spring to early fall, transporting millions of tons.", "citations": {"847379b8-aea2-4369-b4fb-37b79f3e9753_449770659": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Saharan Air Layer, which occurs from June to November, suppresses hurricane development and strength.", "citations": {"847379b8-aea2-4369-b4fb-37b79f3e9753_449770659": 1.0}}, {"text": "The dust transport is approximately 180 million tons per year, or 4.5 million truckloads.", "citations": {"847379b8-aea2-4369-b4fb-37b79f3e9753_449770659": 1.0}}, {"text": "Saharan dust rich in iron and phosphorus fertilizes ocean algae and plankton, supporting marine life.", "citations": {"847379b8-aea2-4369-b4fb-37b79f3e9753_449770659": 1.0}}, {"text": "The dust benefits the Amazon rainforest with extra nutrients, but causes hazy skies and minor allergy symptoms in Texas.", "citations": {"847379b8-aea2-4369-b4fb-37b79f3e9753_449770659": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Saharan dust storm carries harmful bacteria and fungi into North America.", "citations": {"958ae1ee-19d5-41c4-8e42-0583f3ed6841_957102541": 1.0}}, {"text": "The 2020 US experienced the largest Saharan dust storm ever recorded, dubbed \"Godzilla\", highlighting climate change's impact on dust storms.", "citations": {"958ae1ee-19d5-41c4-8e42-0583f3ed6841_957102541": 1.0}}, {"text": "Saharan dust helps regulate the climate, but can harm local environments, coral reefs, and human health.", "citations": {"958ae1ee-19d5-41c4-8e42-0583f3ed6841_957102541": 1.0}}, {"text": "Saharan dust storms carry pollutants and pathogens across continents, affecting ecosystems and climate patterns.", "citations": {"97394a3d-d49a-4762-b01a-724729885709_663017373": 1.0}}, {"text": "Dust storms can cool the Earth's surface and transport microorganisms and nutrients to remote ecosystems.", "citations": {"97394a3d-d49a-4762-b01a-72472988570