{"metadata": {"team_id": "encourage", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1019", "run_id": "encourage-crop"}, "responses": [{"text": "Tai Chi improves balance and reduces the risk of falls in older adults.", "citations": {"0f5cd105-7572-4a55-9c42-607d1c65be3d_663764653": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi combines physical movement, meditation, and deep breathing to improve health and reduce fall risk.", "citations": {"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624": 1.0}}, {"text": "The World Health Organization recommends 150-300 minutes of moderate-intensity aerobic exercise per week, achievable through regular Tai Chi practice, for fall prevention.", "citations": {"4502ea6b-f423-4f08-b3e9-2c45e7a80185_337609787": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi classes are suitable for all ages and can help older adults improve balance and reduce fall risk.", "citations": {"8138d416-ceaa-43d3-a92d-7ad903317f2b_135477836": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi has been adapted for individuals with limited mobility, such as those with dementia or Parkinson's disease, to improve coordination and balance.", "citations": {"14b74b2e-eb4c-4316-a13f-2b94ab1cae1a_760925045": 1.0}}, {"text": "The optimal duration of Tai Chi practice for fall prevention is unclear, but one study suggests 40 minutes per class.", "citations": {"8138d416-ceaa-43d3-a92d-7ad903317f2b_135477836": 1.0}}, {"text": "A 12-week Tai Chi course can reduce waist circumference and improve overall health.", "citations": {"41541b00-f7b4-4a15-8ec7-2d7431c26695_263273629": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi can be adapted for older adults with mobility issues by incorporating sitting exercises and upper body movements.", "citations": {"0b094b42-59fb-428c-ae72-cce9d264a029_188247683": 1.0}}, {"text": "Digital technology can increase access to Tai Chi instruction for older adults through virtual classes and mobile apps.", "citations": {"4dd0fea7-d3a4-424d-9633-57166bb47fcf_1047010706": 1.0}}, {"text": "Mobile apps can motivate older adults to practice Tai Chi, improving physical stability and reducing fall risk.", "citations": {"73578dea-46ff-4ea8-bef0-411024d49f39_18163632": 1.0}}, {"text": "Virtual classes provide an alternative for those with mobility issues to participate in Tai Chi.", "citations": {"73578dea-46ff-4ea8-bef0-411024d49f39_18163632": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi is a valuable exercise option for older adults, offering physical and mental health benefits and adaptable to varying mobility and cognitive levels.", "citations": {"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624": 1.0}}], "references": ["14b74b2e-eb4c-4316-a13f-2b94ab1cae1a_760925045", "2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624", "8138d416-ceaa-43d3-a92d-7ad903317f2b_135477836", "0f5cd105-7572-4a55-9c42-607d1c65be3d_663764653", "4502ea6b-f423-4f08-b3e9-2c45e7a80185_337609787", "0b094b42-59fb-428c-ae72-cce9d264a029_188247683", "73578dea-46ff-4ea8-bef0-411024d49f39_18163632", "4dd0fea7-d3a4-424d-9633-57166bb47fcf_1047010706", "41541b00-f7b4-4a15-8ec7-2d7431c26695_263273629"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "encourage", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1020", "run_id": "encourage-crop"}, "responses": [{"text": "Tai Chi is a low-impact, slow-moving exercise that has been shown to improve balance, strength, and flexibility in older adults, making it an effective method for reducing the risk of falls.", "citations": {"0f5cd105-7572-4a55-9c42-607d1c65be3d_663764653": 1.0}}, {"text": "The practice of Tai Chi combines physical movement, breathing techniques, and meditation to promote relaxation, balance, and overall well-being.", "citations": {"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624": 1.0}}, {"text": "Regular Tai Chi practice has been found to reduce the risk of falls in older adults by improving balance, alleviating degenerative arthritis symptoms, and enhancing cognitive brain function.", "citations": {"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi has also been shown to improve lung function in patients with chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD) and to benefit patients with Parkinson's disease by improving balance and mobility.", "citations": {"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624": 1.0}}, {"text": "In addition to its physical benefits, Tai Chi has a relaxing and meditative effect on users, which can help reduce stress and improve overall mental health.", "citations": {"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624": 1.0}}, {"text": "The World Health Organization recommends at least 150-300 minutes of moderate-intensity exercise per week for fall prevention, and exercising at least three times a week is beneficial for balance and anti-fall activity.", "citations": {"4502ea6b-f423-4f08-b3e9-2c45e7a80185_337609787": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi can be modified to accommodate individuals with varying levels of mobility, including those who use wheelchairs or have cognitive impairments, making it an accessible form of exercise for older adults.", "citations": {"6bb86295-c49b-4797-ab4b-5652344f2d4a_686292122": 1.0}}, {"text": "Caregivers can play a crucial role in establishing anti-fall habits and providing support for older adults to reduce their risk of falls, and can help modify Tai Chi programs to meet the unique needs of their loved ones.", "citations": {"fe956ae4-45c2-4ede-b6fc-27c44b025b5e_30089767": 1.0}}, {"text": "Overall, Tai Chi is a safe, effective, and accessible form of exercise that can be used to reduce the risk of falls and improve overall physical and mental health in older adults.", "citations": {"184485a7-25df-4efa-b2f3-f28ae72d25e3_199781782": 1.0}}, {"text": "The scientific evidence suggests that Tai Chi can be a valuable tool for reducing falls and improving physical stability in older adults, and can be adapted to accommodate individuals with mobility or cognitive limitations.", "citations": {"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi programs can be integrated into existing healthcare systems, and can be used in conjunction with other forms of exercise and therapy to provide a comprehensive approach to fall prevention.", "citations": {"2439fd89-1f9c-4808-8076-189ff603946d_829707379": 1.0}}, {"text": "By incorporating Tai Chi into their exercise routine, older adults can reduce their risk of falls, improve their overall health and well-being, and maintain their independence and quality of life.", "citations": {"184485a7-25df-4efa-b2f3-f28ae72d25e3_199781782": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi is a cost-effective and low-cost health activity that can be done anywhere without special equipment, making it an accessible form of exercise for older adults.", "citations": {"7d2c7153-063e-43b4-a650-65f1d27669c8_63988517": 1.0}}, {"text": "The practice of Tai Chi has been shown to lower blood pressure, improve cardiovascular health, and enhance cognitive function, making it a valuable tool for promoting healthy aging.", "citations": {"b387b7e2-f045-452b-8758-c89e0f69c760_775838414": 1.0}}, {"text": "Overall, the evidence suggests that Tai Chi is a safe, effective, and accessible form of exercise that can be used to reduce the risk of falls and improve overall physical and mental health in older adults.", "citations": {"184485a7-25df-4efa-b2f3-f28ae72d25e3_199781782": 1.0}}], "references": ["6bb86295-c49b-4797-ab4b-5652344f2d4a_686292122", "184485a7-25df-4efa-b2f3-f28ae72d25e3_199781782", "7d2c7153-063e-43b4-a650-65f1d27669c8_63988517", "2439fd89-1f9c-4808-8076-189ff603946d_829707379", "2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624", "b387b7e2-f045-452b-8758-c89e0f69c760_775838414", "fe956ae4-45c2-4ede-b6fc-27c44b025b5e_30089767", "4502ea6b-f423-4f08-b3e9-2c45e7a80185_337609787", "0f5cd105-7572-4a55-9c42-607d1c65be3d_663764653"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "encourage", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1021", "run_id": "encourage-crop"}, "responses": [{"text": "Tai Chi improves strength, balance, and coordination, helping to prevent falls in older adults.", "citations": {"0f5cd105-7572-4a55-9c42-607d1c65be3d_663764653": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi reduces fall risk and alleviates symptoms of degenerative arthritis, improves lung function, and benefits Parkinson's patients by improving balance.", "citations": {"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi can be modified to suit individual needs, making it accessible for older adults with varying physical abilities.", "citations": {"14b74b2e-eb4c-4316-a13f-2b94ab1cae1a_760925045": 1.0}}, {"text": "Practicing Tai Chi three times a week for 12 weeks has been found to have significant health benefits for balance and fall risk.", "citations": {"41541b00-f7b4-4a15-8ec7-2d7431c26695_263273629": 1.0}}, {"text": "The World Health Organization recommends at least 150 minutes of moderate-intensity exercise, such as Tai Chi, per week to prevent falls in elderly individuals.", "citations": {"4502ea6b-f423-4f08-b3e9-2c45e7a80185_337609787": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi benefits older adults by reducing waist circumference, improving lung function, and enhancing cognitive brain function.", "citations": {"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi improves sleep quality, removes blood stasis, and activates circulation, reducing the risk of falls.", "citations": {"31918ed2-62bc-4739-8e23-6eefc0cb0d67_37632800": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi is a convenient and accessible tool for fall prevention that can be practiced anywhere.", "citations": {"31918ed2-62bc-4739-8e23-6eefc0cb0d67_37632800": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi effectively improves mobility and prevents falls in older adults with regular practice.", "citations": {"184485a7-25df-4efa-b2f3-f28ae72d25e3_199781782": 1.0}}, {"text": "Instructors and caregivers play a crucial role in delivering high-quality Tai Chi programs through personalized instruction and support.", "citations": {"5c1162ae-4b10-4556-b59e-5a30440f6c83_159992918": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi improves physical stability and prevents falls.", "citations": {"8138d416-ceaa-43d3-a92d-7ad903317f2b_135477836": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi can improve cardiovascular health, flexibility, and calmness, reducing fall risk.", "citations": {"b387b7e2-f045-452b-8758-c89e0f69c760_775838414": 1.0}}, {"text": "Aging is irreversible, but exercise, like Tai Chi, improves endurance, balance, and prevents functional decline.", "citations": {"cf237750-b384-48ad-85be-e9e241319e81_464746224": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi improves stability and overall health in older adults with balance problems.", "citations": {"eac7354a-8d3a-4125-a99c-ff8769c17923_331358921": 1.0}}, {"text": "Older adults must receive medical clearance from a doctor before participating in Tai Chi programs.", "citations": {"4f97a883-9184-494f-a64a-ca670b25b897_49035528": 1.0}}, {"text": "Customized exercise courses help older adults improve physical function and reduce fall risk.", "citations": {"4f97a883-9184-494f-a64a-ca670b25b897_49035528": 1.0}}], "references": ["cf237750-b384-48ad-85be-e9e241319e81_464746224", "0f5cd105-7572-4a55-9c42-607d1c65be3d_663764653", "8138d416-ceaa-43d3-a92d-7ad903317f2b_135477836", "4f97a883-9184-494f-a64a-ca670b25b897_49035528", "4502ea6b-f423-4f08-b3e9-2c45e7a80185_337609787", "14b74b2e-eb4c-4316-a13f-2b94ab1cae1a_760925045", "eac7354a-8d3a-4125-a99c-ff8769c17923_331358921", "b387b7e2-f045-452b-8758-c89e0f69c760_775838414", "2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624", "184485a7-25df-4efa-b2f3-f28ae72d25e3_199781782", "31918ed2-62bc-4739-8e23-6eefc0cb0d67_37632800", "41541b00-f7b4-4a15-8ec7-2d7431c26695_263273629", "5c1162ae-4b10-4556-b59e-5a30440f6c83_159992918"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "encourage", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1022", "run_id": "encourage-crop"}, "responses": [{"text": "Tai Chi improves mobility and prevents falls in older adults by enhancing balance, strength, and flexibility.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Tai Chi can reduce the risk of falls in older adults by 45% by improving balance and coordination.", "citations": {"0f5cd105-7572-4a55-9c42-607d1c65be3d_663764653": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi has been shown to improve balance and reduce the risk of falls in older adults, with a pooled odds ratio of 0.55.", "citations": {"184485a7-25df-4efa-b2f3-f28ae72d25e3_199781782": 1.0}}, {"text": "The American and British Geriatrics Societies recommend Tai Chi to improve balance and prevent falls in older adults.", "citations": {"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624": 1.0}}, {"text": "To achieve the benefits of Tai Chi, older adults should practice it at least three times a week for 40-60 minutes per session.", "citations": {"41541b00-f7b4-4a15-8ec7-2d7431c26695_263273629": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi can be modified to accommodate different physical abilities and practiced in various settings.", "citations": {"460b5c39-c401-4e48-9f9d-49a3fd391e5d_153526772": 1.0}}, {"text": "Healthcare providers play a crucial role in recommending exercise for older adults with physical limitations to increase muscle mass and limb balance.", "citations": {"80c8da15-5fa3-4f38-8fa6-3c8ddc7d04f2_904596165": 1.0}}, {"text": "Instructors guiding elderly in exercise require training and certification to work with older adults, including those who are disabled or mentally retarded.", "citations": {"8138d416-ceaa-43d3-a92d-7ad903317f2b_135477836": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi is a safe and effective exercise for improving balance and coordination in seniors.", "citations": {"97b014c9-d996-4206-b240-6c9c6a4b3ac0_531746640": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi practice is typically recommended for 5-10 minutes, 2-3 times a day.", "citations": {"fe956ae4-45c2-4ede-b6fc-27c44b025b5e_30089767": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi exercises can be tailored to individual needs by modifying intensity, duration, and movement type.", "citations": {"0086bf3e-329d-4d2f-a345-e11c18285f29_318716116": 1.0}}, {"text": "Older adults with physical limitations can benefit from Tai Chi exercises that improve balance, strength, and flexibility.", "citations": {"5ddca39e-4b17-4d23-a99e-f1b04dac5bf9_1020082342": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi exercises can incorporate assistive devices like canes or walkers for added support and stability for older adults with balance problems.", "citations": {"bc9d8a85-ac6a-49d7-ad15-c535b79a0654_46520525": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi exercises can be tailored to address specific health conditions like arthritis, diabetes, or stroke.", "citations": {"4502ea6b-f423-4f08-b3e9-2c45e7a80185_337609787": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tailored Tai Chi exercises can improve balance, reduce falls, and enhance physical function in older adults with physical limitations.", "citations": {"460b5c39-c401-4e48-9f9d-49a3fd391e5d_154687180": 1.0}}, {"text": "Successful Tai Chi exercise tailoring requires a qualified instructor with experience adapting for older adults with physical limitations or balance problems.", "citations": {"d7cd9455-835d-41e2-892b-cf8a895b12c6_35666433": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tailored Tai Chi exercises can provide a safe and enjoyable way for older adults to improve their physical stability, balance, and overall health.", "citations": {"eac7354a-8d3a-4125-a99c-ff8769c17923_331358921": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi practice can help reduce the risk of falls in older adults by improving balance and muscle strength.", "citations": {"245fa441-2e94-44fe-b953-9f09a184a0c7_915527216": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi can improve cardiovascular health, essential for overall well-being.", "citations": {"449f0a8d-af6e-45ab-9d34-7c04ef0a662c_381950490": 1.0}}, {"text": "Older adults should consult healthcare providers before starting Tai Chi to ensure it's safe.", "citations": {"b387b7e2-f045-452b-8758-c89e0f69c760_775838414": 1.0}}, {"text": "Warm-up and moderate exercise can help prevent muscle strain or joint sprain, especially in older adults.", "citations": {"cf237750-b384-48ad-85be-e9e241319e81_464746224": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi equipment can strengthen upper limbs, but older adults should choose it based on their height and ability.", "citations": {"31918ed2-62bc-4739-8e23-6eefc0cb0d67_37632800": 1.0}}, {"text": "Older adults should exercise with moderate rhythm, smooth breathing, and stop if feeling unwell.", "citations": {"6225cdcd-d1ff-4058-aa7b-7422561fd745_860203953": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi reduces fall risk and alleviates arthritis symptoms in older adults by improving balance and relieving knee stiffness and pain.", "citations": {"0b094b42-59fb-428c-ae72-cce9d264a029_188247683": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi improves lung function in COPD patients and enhances balance and mobility in those with Parkinson's disease.", "citations": {"73578dea-46ff-4ea8-bef0-411024d49f39_18163632": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi enhances cognitive function, reduces stress, and has a calming effect, benefiting dementia patients.", "citations": {"a9da1cd3-8356-4637-b1af-02ba8245cc11_251249146": 1.0}}, {"text": "Older adults are at increased fracture risk from falls due to loose bones, making low-intensity exercises like Tai Chi recommended.", "citations": {"19514fda-10c6-4a39-b83e-29d15c745b43_238493792": 1.0}}, {"text": "Elderly should minimize outdoor activities in snow and ice and prioritize indoor ones in winter.", "citations": {"b1a523db-1455-4f1c-a40e-21bbfb74d854_863396891": 1.0}}, {"text": "Low-intensity sports like Tai Chi are suitable for older adults, while high-risk activities like skiing and skating should be avoided.", "citations": {"d8ac0c44-b1b6-425e-af66-6637a0b90fbf_818892816": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi reduces waist circumference and the risk of type 2 diabetes and cardiovascular disease in older adults with central obesity.", "citations": {"f3c1d887-b09b-41ff-aa6a-d1efb89c36e3_443991890": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi improves metabolic health and increases high-density cholesterol in older adults.", "citations": {"ee16053d-b66f-4aa5-8d9f-f209bd3bb335_727184557": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi is a low-impact exercise suitable for older adults with mobility issues.", "citations": {"317499d9-2f34-4afc-a962-a6f531f75981_71163728": 1.0}}, {"text": "Elderly at risk of falling and those with chronic diseases should seek guidance from experienced teachers and doctors before practicing Tai Chi.", "citations": {"136d9e34-9bc5-45d7-98c8-9aa11fa5c0be_504773949": 1.0}}, {"text": "The practice environment should be clean and quiet, and older adults should practice on a moderately full stomach.", "citations": {"a874023e-781f-4440-9c1e-f8647ce2dc46_1056673632": 1.0}}, {"text": "Older adults with chronic diseases should consult a doctor before practicing sitting eight-duan.", "citations": {"6bb86295-c49b-4797-ab4b-5652344f2d4a_686292122": 1.0}}, {"text": "Elderly should start exercise gradually and increase intensity and duration over time.", "citations": {"c5eebcc7-8fbe-4ce6-ab16-cd7e78c61c30_247889517": 1.0}}, {"text": "Older adults can start with light exercises like tai chi and use mobile apps to track their progress.", "citations": {"4f97a883-9184-494f-a64a-ca670b25b897_49035528": 1.0}}, {"text": "Older adults can reduce injury risk by choosing enjoyable exercises like brisk walking.", "citations": {"765f6998-50e6-42d0-b3c8-ed3d39896f44_326759851": 1.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi helps reduce fall risk in older adults, and older adults should exercise indoors during bad weather.", "citations": {"7e7a1919-3e71-49a8-b572-a342557a73dc_276098024": 1.0}}, {"text": "Taijiquan and Baduanjin exercises can help prevent falls by strengthening balance and muscle strength.", "citations": {"e9e88feb-fe4c-4b14-9a0e-e6455c754862_489536215": 1.0}}, {"text": "Home adaptations and anti-skid treatments can reduce fall risk.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "People with air deficiency should avoid long-term exercise, especially at night or in cold environments.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "High-temperature exercise is harmful to people with yin and virtual body, and outdoor exercise in summer can cause dizziness and heat stroke.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Exercise should be controlled within one hour, with Tai Chi recommended, and avoided at night.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "People with poor blood quality should avoid exercising outdoors in summer or in cold environments.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Tai Chi improves balance, reducing fall risk in older adults.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Tai Chi can be modified for those with balance problems using support.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Chair-based Tai Chi can be done at home with minimal equipment, helping those with mobility limitations.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Chair-based Tai Chi exercises can accommodate severe mobility limitations and improve cardiopulmonary function.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Support from chairs can aid those with balance problems and modify exercises to increase difficulty.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Tai Chi exercises can help relieve physical and mental stress.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Modified Tai Chi can improve muscle endurance, strength, and be adapted for seniors with disabilities.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Wall exercises support elderly with balance problems and can be used with Tai Chi.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Chair-based exercises can be adjusted to suit individual ability and difficulty, including for those with mobility limitations.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Tai Chi helps reduce falls in older adults with balance problems, and improves overall health and mood.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Balance training targets core muscles, legs, and buttocks, and can be modified for support.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Good balance, which relies on eyes and