 "citations": {"a25dd587-a7b4-4e54-9d1c-6dd2e05badf2_419108617": 1.0}}, {"text": "Erdogan has threatened to part ways with the EU and proposed a parallel framework for Turkey-EU relations.", "citations": {"a25dd587-a7b4-4e54-9d1c-6dd2e05badf2_419108617": 1.0}}, {"text": "The EU has blocked Turkey's accession over human rights concerns.", "citations": {"a25dd587-a7b4-4e54-9d1c-6dd2e05badf2_419108617": 1.0}}, {"text": "Turkey's relations with the US and EU may deteriorate due to economic troubles and Erdogan's opposition to Finland and Sweden's NATO entry and Greece's Aegean island militarization.", "citations": {"bab7e9d6-7690-4a57-ae3b-2d73a74a3638_144170093": 1.0}}, {"text": "The US should prepare for aggravation with Ankara due to potential opposition from Erdogan.", "citations": {"bab7e9d6-7690-4a57-ae3b-2d73a74a3638_144170093": 1.0}}, {"text": "Turkey's actions may help Russia and weaken Western cooperation.", "citations": {"bab7e9d6-7690-4a57-ae3b-2d73a74a3638_144170093": 1.0}}, {"text": "Erdogan may scapegoat Western countries for Turkey's economic difficulties, increasing tension.", "citations": {"bab7e9d6-7690-4a57-ae3b-2d73a74a3638_144170093": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Hagia Sophia controversy may distract from economic issues, as Erdogan's government considers converting it to a mosque to appease domestic supporters.", "citations": {"d0d4acd7-74b5-467f-9c78-985c6a08a9e5_893345947": 1.0}}, {"text": "The US prioritizes protecting Middle Eastern Christian minorities.", "citations": {"d0d4acd7-74b5-467f-9c78-985c6a08a9e5_893345947": 1.0}}, {"text": "Erdogan's shift away from Western partners may harm Turkey's EU and Western relations.", "citations": {"d0d4acd7-74b5-467f-9c78-985c6a08a9e5_893345947": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Hagia Sophia controversy highlights the complex relationship between cultural heritage and religious identity in Turkey and globally.", "citations": {"97d76ff6-1c05-45d5-ba89-88ccc0122e21_491069692": 1.0}}, {"text": "The site's UNESCO World Heritage designation and historical significance make it a sensitive and contested space.", "citations": {"3886289d-abc9-433e-9ed3-f3bd8c9a9f7d_513279190": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Turkish government has reimposed an entrance fee and restricted access to exert control over the site.", "citations": {"7c91a665-2672-4d9b-8eae-3ec3168be312_904357446": 1.0}}, {"text": "Headsets in 23 languages have been implemented to cater to the site's diverse tourist group.", "citations": {"3886289d-abc9-433e-9ed3-f3bd8c9a9f7d_513279190": 1.0}}, {"text": "Restoration work and new security systems have improved the tourist experience.", "citations": {"3886289d-abc9-433e-9ed3-f3bd8c9a9f7d_513279190": 1.0}}, {"text": "Covering the mosaics and frescoes during prayer times is a compromise between the site's religious and cultural significance.", "citations": {"76e3d61c-e991-43a2-8ebe-637114089506_291378229": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Anatolian Youth Association played a key role in Hagia Sophia's conversion into a mosque.", "citations": {"d0d4acd7-74b5-467f-9c78-985c6a08a9e5_893345947": 1.0}}, {"text": "The American Council for the Liberation of Hagia Sophia demands the site be returned to its former museum status.", "citations": {"78791118-f9c5-4ecd-b7a2-e57dcecfb197_751571096": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Pope and Orthodox Patriarch have expressed dismay over Hagia Sophia's conversion into a mosque.", "citations": {"a8d17c9c-d219-4c0f-b2b9-f79c754a6d8c_960510274": 1.0}}, {"text": "The first prayer at the site was attended by 1000-1500 people, with COVID-19 quarantine measures in place.", "citations": {"a8d17c9c-d219-4c0f-b2b9-f79c754a6d8c_960510274": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Turkish court's ruling that the 1934 conversion was illegal led to the site's reconversion into a mosque.", "citations": {"a8d17c9c-d219-4c0f-b2b9-f79c754a6d8c_960510274": 1.0}}, {"text": "Foreign tourists pay \u20ac25 to enter, while Turkish citizens enter for free.", "citations": {"5f313598-c9ac-40a3-8bae-106d6564ae87_210914181": 1.0}}, {"text": "Entrance fees will fund cultural asset preservation.", "citations": {"97d76ff6-1c05-45d5-ba89-88ccc0122e21_491069692": 1.0}}, {"text": "The site's new management plan aims to improve visiting hours, safety, and visitor density.", "citations": {"f81149b2-9efa-411c-b8fa-ed1ba6062f6f_619383984": 1.0}}, {"text": "The site information will be provided in 16 languages.", "citations": {"f81149b2-9efa-411c-b8fa-ed1ba6062f6f_619383984": 1.0}}, {"text": "The site", "citations": {}}], "references": ["029e4bd8-6472-4e81-9ede-03ad058f256d_794435160", "9ba1561a-fc64-4cc3-b0ee-218d2b7a3e8d_609947018", "d0d4acd7-74b5-467f-9c78-985c6a08a9e5_893345947", "76e3d61c-e991-43a2-8ebe-637114089506_291378229", "f81149b2-9efa-411c-b8fa-ed1ba6062f6f_619383984", "47ee13b4-a42c-4fff-a4f2-4d7ad173b2ea_831248943", "a4541930-bdd4-4c2c-aecc-f835cb26d5a7_175833066", "1728cb60-f6d4-4608-9008-e098d1b713bf_3761550", "97d76ff6-1c05-45d5-ba89-88ccc0122e21_491069692", "7c91a665-2672-4d9b-8eae-3ec3168be312_904357446", "bab7e9d6-7690-4a57-ae3b-2d73a74a3638_144170093", "3886289d-abc9-433e-9ed3-f3bd8c9a9f7d_513279190", "dc7d1e14-9026-4142-8352-b56898791c5a_838665307", "7bd7f65b-ba9c-4b70-82b0-3180fa15662a_964461365", "36db8615-aa07-4391-a3f5-098dba27f295_1069312408", "5f313598-c9ac-40a3-8bae-106d6564ae87_210914181", "cdd3edc3-554e-4d45-a21a-8e8aa2745af8_463983220", "6520a8e4-2d97-4c78-8f05-4f048241b9f6_105665812", "78791118-f9c5-4ecd-b7a2-e57dcecfb197_751571096", "a8d17c9c-d219-4c0f-b2b9-f79c754a6d8c_960510274", "d1e9ee01-e907-4819-a825-03adca8d534f_94987191", "a25dd587-a7b4-4e54-9d1c-6dd2e05badf2_419108617"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "encourage", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1041", "run_id": "encourage-crop"}, "responses": [{"text": "Ayurveda has been found effective in treating diseases like diabetes, hypertension, and cancer by maintaining balance and harmony in the body.", "citations": {"57a4cab9-1b23-4ded-946b-11646bce1b5f_855891334": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Indian government plans to operationalize 12,500 Ayush health and wellness centers by 2023-24, allocating Rs 719.70 crore to southern states under the National Ayush Mission.", "citations": {"2a71159d-8419-47be-a5f6-27e2d320f5da_156354955": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ayurvedic herbs like turmeric, cinnamon, fenugreek, and ginger have anti-diabetic properties and can help lower blood sugar levels.", "citations": {"57a4cab9-1b23-4ded-946b-11646bce1b5f_855891334": 1.0, "6d168c6d-dcc5-4ceb-834e-fe25abd663c5_178517965": 0.5, "6cc6aaad-b699-4ef6-b206-d502fa60a4e9_978772489": 0.25}}, {"text": "Ashwagandha, an Indian herbal medicine, reduces anxiety, stress, and fatigue, and improves muscle strength, with clinical trials studying its effects on chronic diseases.", "citations": {"ce13ec75-5d14-4993-a8f7-c31c1539b04b_1051680076": 1.0}}, {"text": "The World Health Organization recognizes traditional medicine as a primary resort for millions and is working to establish safe usage standards.", "citations": {"aec0ad01-6840-40c7-b34e-5e9f8b9060f5_461874472": 1.0, "8ab3ddad-35b5-48f8-a58e-56a49840ca41_799531423": 0.5}}, {"text": "India seeks to include Ayurveda in the WHO's ICD-11 list with Ministry of Ayush support.", "citations": {"e2101fe3-e219-47c1-8300-449bef7dfe12_68754735": 1.0}}, {"text": "Regulatory frameworks for traditional Indian herbal medicines vary globally, with Uganda having regulations, but the UK and US lacking them.", "citations": {"e69d7e19-5d46-4680-a522-a289c0f87162_321290577": 1.0, "e740d601-b53e-4635-9992-3e8936b06287_572584438": 0.5}}, {"text": "The National Drug Authority in Uganda and India's Ministry of Ayush regulate and promote herbal medicines to ensure safety and healthy lifestyles.", "citations": {"2a71159d-8419-47be-a5f6-27e2d320f5da_156354955": 1.0, "e69d7e19-5d46-4680-a522-a289c0f87162_321290577": 0.5}}, {"text": "Ayurveda has been studied for various diseases, but can cause heavy metal poisoning, highlighting the need for quality control and safety measures.", "citations": {"e02c016b-9a11-4d76-93bc-c339103d09ea_364440793": 1.0}}, {"text": "Traditional Indian herbal medicines like turmeric, ashwagandha, and neem have various health benefits, including reducing inflammation and aiding in disease treatment.", "citations": {"6d168c6d-dcc5-4ceb-834e-fe25abd663c5_178517965": 1.0, "ce13ec75-5d14-4993-a8f7-c31c1539b04b_1051680076": 0.5, "3a5cc032-c483-4fab-9c77-46883738f736_76360426": 0.25}}, {"text": "The WHO and the Indian government are collaborating to develop standards for traditional Indian herbal medicines to ensure their safe and effective use.", "citations": {"cb9ef0c6-8b7e-40ec-a20a-a356d3083fe7_261399576": 1.0, "e2101fe3-e219-47c1-8300-449bef7dfe12_68754735": 0.5}}, {"text": "The Indian government and WHO are collaborating to promote safe and effective traditional medicine through evidence-based practices and research.", "citations": {"cb9ef0c6-8b7e-40ec-a20a-a356d3083fe7_261399576": 1.0, "aec0ad01-6840-40c7-b34e-5e9f8b9060f5_461874472": 0.5}}, {"text": "Greater regulation of herbal supplements is needed, especially in the UK and US, to prevent health problems and deaths.", "citations": {"e740d601-b53e-4635-9992-3e8936b06287_572584438": 1.0}}], "references": ["aec0ad01-6840-40c7-b34e-5e9f8b9060f5_461874472", "e740d601-b53e-4635-9992-3e8936b06287_572584438", "2a71159d-8419-47be-a5f6-27e2d320f5da_156354955", "e02c016b-9a11-4d76-93bc-c339103d09ea_364440793", "57a4cab9-1b23-4ded-946b-11646bce1b5f_855891334", "3a5cc032-c483-4fab-9c77-46883738f736_76360426", "cb9ef0c6-8b7e-40ec-a20a-a356d3083fe7_261399576", "6d168c6d-dcc5-4ceb-834e-fe25abd663c5_178517965", "6cc6aaad-b699-4ef6-b206-d502fa60a4e9_978772489", "e2101fe3-e219-47c1-8300-449bef7dfe12_68754735", "ce13ec75-5d14-4993-a8f7-c31c1539b04b_1051680076", "e69d7e19-5d46-4680-a522-a289c0f87162_321290577", "8ab3ddad-35b5-48f8-a58e-56a49840ca41_799531423"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "encourage", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1042", "run_id": "encourage-crop"}, "responses": [{"text": "Ayurveda has been found effective in treating diseases like diabetes with limited side effects.", "citations": {"57a4cab9-1b23-4ded-946b-11646bce1b5f_855891334": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Indian government supports integrating Ayurveda with modern medicine through institutions like the National Commission for Indian System of Medicine and the Ministry of Ayush.", "citations": {"2a71159d-8419-47be-a5f6-27e2d320f5da_156354955": 1.0}}, {"text": "Turmeric, an Ayurvedic medicine, helps control blood sugar levels and mitigate the effects of modern diabetes drugs.", "citations": {"57a4cab9-1b23-4ded-946b-11646bce1b5f_855891334": 1.0}}, {"text": "Indian herbal medicines like ashwagandha reduce anxiety, stress, and fatigue, and improve muscle strength, with a UK clinical trial underway to study its effects on long Covid.", "citations": {"ce13ec75-5d14-4993-a8f7-c31c1539b04b_1051680076": 1.0}}, {"text": "Combining Indian herbal medicines with Western medications can have benefits, like reduced cardiovascular mortality, but also risks, including liver injury and medication interactions.", "citations": {"4c64fdbd-f44c-4c26-83c3-61e9b7238db1_111548416": 1.0}}, {"text": "The WHO recognizes traditional Indian medicine, including Ayurveda, as a healthcare supplement, with institutions like the All India Institute of Ayurveda researching its development.", "citations": {"7c35d59b-3417-4232-97ca-d685314ade3f_354844377": 1.0}}, {"text": "The WHO has a centre in India for traditional medicine research, backed by a $250 million Indian government commitment.", "citations": {"cb9ef0c6-8b7e-40ec-a20a-a356d3083fe7_261399576": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ayurvedic herbs like basil, cinnamon, and fenugreek have anti-diabetic properties, regulating blood sugar and improving insulin sensitivity, with cinnamon shown to lower fasting plasma glucose and hemoglobin A1c levels.", "citations": {"6d168c6d-dcc5-4ceb-834e-fe25abd663c5_178517965": 1.0}}, {"text": "Indian herbal medicines like ginger, licorice, and cinnamon can interact with Western medications, such as blood thinners, and cause potential risks.", "citations": {"a7201d04-49e1-4445-8968-39b803cd4996_550704310": 1.0}}, {"text": "Indian herbal medicines, including oil pulling, may help treat diseases like diabetes, anxiety, and cardiovascular conditions.", "citations": {"1146fd9a-a273-494b-a044-f8edfa8dce7d_287672637": 1.0}}, {"text": "Turmeric, used in Indian herbal medicine, has anti-inflammatory properties that help lower blood sugar levels, with its key component curcumin regulating inflammatory pathways.", "citations": {"57a4cab9-1b23-4ded-946b-11646bce1b5f_855891334": 1.0}}, {"text": "The interactions between Indian herbal medicines and Western medications are not fully understood and require further research to determine their safety and efficacy.", "citations": {"b51c5629-4cd6-4e05-8289-2040fe52dddd_241009458": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ashwagandha, an Indian herbal medicine, reduces anxiety, stress, and fatigue, and improves muscle strength, with a UK clinical trial underway to study its effects on long Covid.", "citations": {"ce13ec75-5d14-4993-a8f7-c31c1539b04b_1051680076": 1.0}}, {"text": "The World Health Organization supports research on traditional medicine, including Ayurveda and herbal medicines like ashwagandha, as a healthcare supplement.", "citations": {"ce13ec75-5d14-4993-a8f7-c31c1539b04b_1051680076": 1.0}}, {"text": "Traditional Indian medicine has been found effective in treating various diseases, but further research is needed to determine its safety and efficacy when combined with Western medications.", "citations": {"57a4cab9-1b23-4ded-946b-11646bce1b5f_855891334": 1.0, "ce13ec75-5d14-4993-a8f7-c31c1539b04b_1051680076": 0.5, "e02c016b-9a11-4d76-93bc-c339103d09ea_364440793": 0.25, "7c35d59b-3417-4232-97ca-d685314ade3f_354844377": 0.125, "cb9ef0c6-8b7e-40ec-a20a-a356d3083fe7_261399576": 0.0625, "b51c5629-4cd6-4e05-8289-2040fe52dddd_241009458": 0.03125, "a7201d04-49e1-4445-8968-39b803cd4996_550704310": 0.015625, "1146fd9a-a273-494b-a044-f8edfa8dce7d_287672637": 0.0078125, "4c64fdbd-f44c-4c26-83c3-61e9b7238db1_111548416": 0.00390625}}, {"text": "References:", "citations": {}}, {"text": "The global herbal medicine market is expected to reach USD 371.45 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 8.02%.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Neem tree extract has anti-parasitic and antiviral properties that can help treat COVID-19.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Indian researchers are studying rhododendron arboreum for its antiviral activity against COVID-19 with promising results.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Ayurveda has been found to effectively treat Type 2 diabetes, with turmeric being a key ingredient in maintaining blood sugar levels.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Cardamom has anti-inflammatory properties, making it applicable in treating diseases like respiratory issues and cancer.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Indian herbs like basil, cinnamon, and fenugreek help regulate Type 2 diabetes and reduce blood pressure.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "The \"herb of kings\" treats diseases like malaria, gastric issues, and joint pain with its natural oils.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "HealthRoots uses rare international herbs to treat headaches, stress, and other ailments in the Indian market.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Researchers have identified 400 medicinal plants with anti-diabetic properties, including 21 with prominent anti-hyperglycemic action.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Ashwagandha reduces anxiety and stress, improves muscle strength, and reduces fatigue, with a large UK clinical trial currently underway.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Herbs and spices have anti-inflammatory properties that can help prevent obesity, cardiovascular diseases, and cancer by altering gut microbiota.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Ayurveda treats disease with diet, herbs, and massage, using a balance of three doshas.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "The Indian government supports integrating Ayurveda with modern medicine, allocating Rs 719.70 crore for Ayush development.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Ayurvedic medicine uses a holistic approach, incorporating essential herbs to treat the body, mind, and spirit.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "The California College of Ayurveda offers training in Ayurvedic Medicine, including Ayurvedic Yoga Therapy.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Triphala is an Ayurvedic medicine with antioxidant properties that improves blood flow and reduces cholesterol, blood pressure, and toxins.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "The World Health Organization recognizes Ayurveda, and some hospitals offer Ayurvedic treatments alongside modern medicine.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Ayurvedic remedies like potato juice, yoghurt, aloe vera, and orange peel are used to lighten skin tone and improve complexion.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Vedas Cure offers Ayurvedic remedies for women's health issues, including Garbhashay Dosh, certified by the Uttarakhand Drug Authority.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "The Ministry of AYUSH promotes traditional Indian medicine through various institutions and research centers.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "The National Commission for Indian System of Medicine supports and regulates traditional Indian medicine.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "A Central Research Institute of Yoga & Naturopathy has been established in Dibrugarh.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "The All India Institute of Ayurveda and National Institute of Unani Medicine are examples of research centers for traditional Indian medicine.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "The WHO Global Centre for Traditional Medicine is proposed to be set up in India to standardize research in traditional medicine.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "The centre will study traditional medicine using AI and big data to inform policy.", "citations": {}}