y.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "Indian herbal medicines can interact with Western medications, posing potential risks or benefits.", "citations": {}}, {"text": "[", "citations": {}}], "references": ["a7201d04-49e1-4445-8968-39b803cd4996_550704310", "1146fd9a-a273-494b-a044-f8edfa8dce7d_287672637", "e02c016b-9a11-4d76-93bc-c339103d09ea_364440793", "6d168c6d-dcc5-4ceb-834e-fe25abd663c5_178517965", "2a71159d-8419-47be-a5f6-27e2d320f5da_156354955", "b51c5629-4cd6-4e05-8289-2040fe52dddd_241009458", "57a4cab9-1b23-4ded-946b-11646bce1b5f_855891334", "7c35d59b-3417-4232-97ca-d685314ade3f_354844377", "cb9ef0c6-8b7e-40ec-a20a-a356d3083fe7_261399576", "4c64fdbd-f44c-4c26-83c3-61e9b7238db1_111548416", "ce13ec75-5d14-4993-a8f7-c31c1539b04b_1051680076"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "encourage", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1047", "run_id": "encourage-crop"}, "responses": [{"text": "Ocean acidification affects marine life, including cephalopods and octopuses, by altering their physiology and behavior.", "citations": {"5eaf29bc-9eb3-4678-b6d5-6b31ef609367_520746131": 1.0}}, {"text": "The pH level decreased from 8.3 to 7.9 between the 1980s and 2019, impacting marine ecosystems by reducing shellfish populations and shell size.", "citations": {"4be17bf1-5442-40ce-8ca3-0eee3640016c_480614678": 1.0}}, {"text": "Cephalopods, like octopuses, are vulnerable to ocean changes, including warming, which affects their vision, metabolism, and reproduction.", "citations": {"f681d169-2708-462a-ba28-f689fa1fae4f_169019957": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ocean acidification can affect the nervous systems and behavior of marine animals, including cephalopods.", "citations": {"f785f39e-07b2-4c9d-a70b-ae1bbce61477_283929611": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ocean acidification has increased by 26% since pre-industrial times, with the ocean absorbing 23% of annual anthropogenic CO2 emissions.", "citations": {"fd3cffd4-e1c0-49e9-af0e-b2a04d515360_1027225775": 1.0}}, {"text": "Reducing pollution, promoting seagrass and kelp growth, and implementing place-based actions can help mitigate ocean acidification.", "citations": {"05d3d6bf-6d65-4dbe-b48e-f5a4bbf5218b_773785891": 1.0, "5dbafe29-4476-42c1-a6d5-fad4faa86524_888794707": 0.5, "72c97bcc-1d0e-4811-af80-28bb8339387c_827939974": 0.25, "af4623f9-11e4-4872-acf1-82ab58601269_463596060": 0.125}}, {"text": "Raising awareness and promoting sustainable practices can help mitigate ocean acidification's effects.", "citations": {"5dbafe29-4476-42c1-a6d5-fad4faa86524_888794707": 1.0, "67c5609d-d56f-4dfa-9cac-fc4820422fa9_838476104": 0.5}}, {"text": "Ocean acidification's effects on cephalopods are not well-studied, but ocean warming is known to affect octopus vision.", "citations": {"f681d169-2708-462a-ba28-f689fa1fae4f_169019957": 1.0}}, {"text": "Heat stress reduces vision-related proteins in octopus eyes.", "citations": {"f681d169-2708-462a-ba28-f689fa1fae4f_169019957": 1.0}}, {"text": "Warmer waters accelerate octopus metabolism and reduce their size, potentially impacting their ecological role.", "citations": {"f681d169-2708-462a-ba28-f689fa1fae4f_169019957": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ocean warming alters octopus distribution and reproduction, reducing egg spawn numbers and causing unhatched broods.", "citations": {"f681d169-2708-462a-ba28-f689fa1fae4f_169019957": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ocean acidification affects pteropods, which are crucial for the ocean environment and the food web.", "citations": {"54053584-4dc9-40d0-bbea-8b47295e1d6f_116363246": 1.0}}, {"text": "The ocean contributes $5 trillion to the global economy, with 65.8% of fish stocks at sustainable levels, but has acidified by 26% since pre-industrial times.", "citations": {"fd3cffd4-e1c0-49e9-af0e-b2a04d515360_1027225775": 1.0}}, {"text": "High school climate justice clubs can raise awareness about ocean acidification and inspire action to reduce carbon emissions.", "citations": {"03b8f703-dbe1-45c1-a82d-40c6157ec2a4_856744375": 1.0}}, {"text": "Integrating UN Sustainable Development Goals into the curriculum can raise awareness about ocean acidification and its impacts on marine life.", "citations": {"03b8f703-dbe1-45c1-a82d-40c6157ec2a4_856744375": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ocean acidification is a complex issue requiring a comprehensive approach to address its impacts on marine ecosystems and coastal economies.", "citations": {"67c5609d-d56f-4dfa-9cac-fc4820422fa9_838476104": 1.0}}], "references": ["67c5609d-d56f-4dfa-9cac-fc4820422fa9_838476104", "af4623f9-11e4-4872-acf1-82ab58601269_463596060", "05d3d6bf-6d65-4dbe-b48e-f5a4bbf5218b_773785891", "f785f39e-07b2-4c9d-a70b-ae1bbce61477_283929611", "5dbafe29-4476-42c1-a6d5-fad4faa86524_888794707", "72c97bcc-1d0e-4811-af80-28bb8339387c_827939974", "fd3cffd4-e1c0-49e9-af0e-b2a04d515360_1027225775", "54053584-4dc9-40d0-bbea-8b47295e1d6f_116363246", "03b8f703-dbe1-45c1-a82d-40c6157ec2a4_856744375", "4be17bf1-5442-40ce-8ca3-0eee3640016c_480614678", "f681d169-2708-462a-ba28-f689fa1fae4f_169019957", "5eaf29bc-9eb3-4678-b6d5-6b31ef609367_520746131"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "encourage", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1048", "run_id": "encourage-crop"}, "responses": [{"text": "Ocean acidification is a pressing issue that affects marine life, including cephalopods like cuttlefish, by reducing the availability of calcium carbonate, which is essential for building shells and skeletons.", "citations": {"0f12f37d-8df3-4e5d-90c5-d3860ba8d4a2_872534487": 1.0}}, {"text": "The decrease in pH levels due to ocean acidification can dissolve calcium carbonate shells and skeletons, making it harder for creatures to build shells.", "citations": {"0f12f37d-8df3-4e5d-90c5-d3860ba8d4a2_872534487": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ocean acidification occurs due to excessive carbon dioxide in the atmosphere, which is absorbed by the ocean, causing a decrease in pH levels.", "citations": {"0f12f37d-8df3-4e5d-90c5-d3860ba8d4a2_872534487": 1.0}}, {"text": "Some fish can evolve rapidly to cope with ocean acidification, but there is limited information available on the specific responses of cuttlefish to changes in seawater pH.", "citations": {"5eaf29bc-9eb3-4678-b6d5-6b31ef609367_520746131": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ocean acidification affects marine life physiology and behavior, including changes in genetic transcription and immune function, but the specific impacts on cuttlefish are not well understood.", "citations": {"5eaf29bc-9eb3-4678-b6d5-6b31ef609367_520746131": 1.0}}, {"text": "Pteropods, which are related to cephalopods, are vulnerable to ocean acidification, particularly during winter, and a decrease in their populations can affect the food web and carbon cycle.", "citations": {"54053584-4dc9-40d0-bbea-8b47295e1d6f_116363246": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ocean acidification can also impact the food web and ecosystem functions, such as water filtering and habitat creation, which are provided by invertebrates like cephalopods.", "citations": {"2056ad62-4ce5-4358-9b9d-46e1a757895a_866149019": 1.0}}, {"text": "The combined effects of ocean acidification, warming, and pollution can lead to a decline in cephalopod populations and alter the structure of marine ecosystems.", "citations": {"eabaa8bc-af88-4b73-a1b2-dec0f49336fd_390178312": 1.0}}, {"text": "Cephalopods, such as cuttlefish and squid, play important roles in marine ecosystems, and changes to their populations can have cascading effects on the entire ecosystem.", "citations": {"df0754b4-3eed-49c2-a80a-ff78f49dcdc3_971902444": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ocean conservation efforts are necessary to sustainably use marine resources and to protect vulnerable species, such as cephalopods, from the impacts of ocean acidification and warming.", "citations": {"fd3cffd4-e1c0-49e9-af0e-b2a04d515360_1027225775": 1.0}}, {"text": "The ocean provides important ecosystem services and supports human well-being, and it is essential to take action to mitigate the effects of ocean acidification and warming on marine ecosystems.", "citations": {"fd3cffd4-e1c0-49e9-af0e-b2a04d515360_1027225775": 1.0}}, {"text": "Climate change, which includes ocean acidification and warming, disrupts environmental signals for habitat and food, and can alter ecosystem energy balance and structure.", "citations": {"f785f39e-07b2-4c9d-a70b-ae1bbce61477_283929611": 1.0}}, {"text": "Temperature shifts can change animal behavior and physiology, and can have significant impacts on the survival and reproduction of cephalopods and other marine species.", "citations": {"f785f39e-07b2-4c9d-a70b-ae1bbce61477_283929611": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ocean acidification is predicted to increase by 100-150% by the end of the century, which could have devastating effects on marine life, including cephalopods.", "citations": {"fd3cffd4-e1c0-49e9-af0e-b2a04d515360_1027225775": 1.0}}, {"text": "The lack of specific information on the impacts of ocean acidification on cuttlefish and other cephalopods highlights the need for further research and conservation efforts.", "citations": {"fd3cffd4-e1c0-49e9-af0e-b2a04d515360_1027225775": 1.0}}, {"text": "The United Nations' SDG 14.3 aims to minimize and address ocean acidification, and implementing this goal requires cross-cutting issue embedding and unique approaches by governments.", "citations": {"67c5609d-d56f-4dfa-9cac-fc4820422fa9_838476104": 1.0}}, {"text": "Place-based actions can aid in implementing SDG programs, and partnerships can provide synergies for joint SDG implementation.", "citations": {"05d3d6bf-6d65-4dbe-b48e-f5a4bbf5218b_773785891": 1.0}}, {"text": "Overall, ocean acidification is a significant threat to marine ecosystems, including cephalopods like cuttlefish, and urgent action is needed to mitigate its impacts.", "citations": {"fd3cffd4-e1c0-49e9-af0e-b2a04d515360_1027225775": 1.0}}, {"text": "Unfortunately, there is limited information available on the specific physiological and behavioral responses of cuttlefish to changes in seawater pH.", "citations": {"08ea846b-f3bb-42ce-b419-8728f53a6473_277927334": 1.0}}, {"text": "More research is needed to understand the effects of ocean acidification on cuttlefish and other cephalopods, and to develop effective conservation strategies.", "citations": {"fd3cffd4-e1c0-49e9-af0e-b2a04d515360_1027225775": 1.0}}, {"text": "The search results did not provide specific information on the impacts of ocean acidification on cuttlefish and other cephalopods, highlighting the need for further research.", "citations": {"0f12f37d-8df3-4e5d-90c5-d3860ba8d4a2_872534487": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ocean acidification affects marine life due to high CO2 levels, and some fish evolve rapidly to cope with ocean acidification.", "citations": {"5eaf29bc-9eb3-4678-b6d5-6b31ef609367_520746131": 1.0}}, {"text": "However, the specific impacts of ocean acidification on cuttlefish and other cephalopods are not well understood, and more research is needed to address this knowledge gap.", "citations": {"fd3cffd4-e1c0-49e9-af0e-b2a04d515360_1027225775": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ocean acidification is a complex issue that requires a comprehensive approach to mitigate its impacts on marine ecosystems, including cephalopods like cuttlefish.", "citations": {"67c5609d-d56f-4dfa-9cac-fc4820422fa9_838476104": 1.0}}, {"text": "The establishment of marine protected areas can conserve oceans effectively, and the designation of these areas requires public hearing and approval.", "citations": {"8da4c4f5-a7b0-4c97-b551-8938814654e5_74151378": 1.0}}, {"text": "Kelp deployment on oyster farms can nullify ocean acidification, and kelp cultivation benefits bivalve growth and survival.", "citations": {"af4623f9-11e4-4872-acf1-82ab58601269_463596060": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ocean acidification affects odor tracking in reef fish and sharks, and climate change disrupts environmental signals for habitat and food.", "citations": {"f785f39e-07b2-4c9d-a70b-ae1bbce61477_283929611": 1.0}}, {"text": "Temperature changes disrupt environmental signals for habitat and food, leading to behavioral shifts in animals and ecosystems.", "citations": {"f785f39e-07b2-4c9d-a70b-ae1bbce61477_283929611": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ocean acidification is a consequence of global warming, and it increases water acidity by 26% since pre-industrial times.", "citations": {"fd3cffd4-e1c0-49e9-af0e-b2a04d515360_1027225775": 1.0}}, {"text": "A projected 100-150% acidity increase by the end of the century is expected to have significant effects on marine life.", "citations": {"fd3cffd4-e1c0-49e9-af0e-b2a04d515360_1027225775": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ocean acidification poses a threat to commercial aquaculture and food security, as it affects the growth and survival of many marine species.", "citations": {"0f12f37d-8df3-4e5d-90c5-d3860ba8d4a2_872534487": 1.0}}, {"text": "Fish become suicidal due to climate change, and high acidity leads to fish species loss, with 30% of carbon dioxide emissions being absorbed by water.", "citations": {"266675e3-f638-46d4-9a4f-ba56bf74d262_390364858": 1.0}}, {"text": "Ocean warming and acidification affect Pacific cod's early life stages, with temperature being the dominant stressor.", "citations": {"38bc0ca9-7189-4e60-9649-6082d34b1be5_19527343": 1.0}}, {"text": "Pacific cod growth is fastest at 10\u00b0C, but with high mortality, and ocean warming is a greater threat to Pacific cod than acidification.", "citations": {"38bc0ca9-7189-4e60-9649-6082d34b1be5_19527343": 1.0}}], "references": ["df0754b4-3eed-49c2-a80a-ff78f49dcdc3_971902444", "5eaf29bc-9eb3-4678-b6d5-6b31ef609367_520746131", "08ea846b-f3bb-42ce-b419-8728f53a6473_277927334", "af4623f9-11e4-4872-acf1-82ab58601269_463596060", "eabaa8bc-af88-4b73-a1b2-dec0f49336fd_390178312", "f785f39e-07b2-4c9d-a70b-ae1bbce61477_283929611", "67c5609d-d56f-4dfa-9cac-fc4820422fa9_838476104", "05d3d6bf-6d65-4dbe-b48e-f5a4bbf5218b_773785891", "38bc0ca9-7189-4e60-9649-6082d34b1be5_19527343", "54053584-4dc9-40d0-bbea-8b47295e1d6f_116363246", "fd3cffd4-e1c0-49e9-af0e-b2a04d515360_1027225775", "266675e3-f638-46d4-9a4f-ba56bf74d262_390364858", "2056ad62-4ce5-4358-9b9d-46e1a757895a_866149019", "0f12f37d-8df3-4e5d-90c5-d3860ba8d4a2_872534487", "8da4c4f5-a7b0-4c97-b551-8938814654e5_74151378"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "encourage", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1053", "run_id": "encourage-crop"}, "responses": [{"text": "The US is the largest consumer of avocados, accounting for almost half of global demand.", "citations": {"0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_25051651": 1.0}}, {"text": "Mexico, the world's largest avocado producer, has seen a rise in avocado farming, with 70% of production coming from Michoac\u00e1n.", "citations": {"0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_25051651": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado farming expansion has led to significant environmental concerns, including deforestation, with over 300 square kilometers of Mexican forest converted to plantations between 2018 and 2023.", "citations": {"0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_55923929": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado production consumes around 1,000 liters of water per kilogram, contributing to water depletion in areas where it's prevalent.", "citations": {"9f7babf6-335c-4686-b3fe-7602641d29a4_195587657": 1.0}}, {"text": "The avocado industry is linked to social concerns, including labor exploitation and displacement of indigenous communities, particularly in Mexico.", "citations": {"c4df1771-8297-4414-adac-d7cd6bb376e0_639626865": 1.0}}, {"text": "Certification programs like the Rainforest Alliance promote sustainable avocado farming, reducing deforestation and supporting environmental, social, and economic goals.", "citations": {"9f7babf6-335c-4686-b3fe-7602641d29a4_195587657": 1.0}}, {"text": "Technology innovation, like satellite imaging and drones, can support reforestation and reduce deforestation in areas impacted by avocado farming.", "citations": {"063e477f-f6cb-4caf-92f0-2e8f0ac78ac1_269466826": 1.0}}, {"text": "GLC Cerritos LLC has hired a sustainability director and aims to secure Fair Trade certification to promote sustainable avocado farming practices.", "citations": {"695b759e-d787-4a16-9bc5-9f006dc56478_763886478": 1.0}}, {"text": "The growing demand for avocados has significant economic, environmental, and social implications, requiring a multi-faceted approach to address these concerns.", "citations": {"99536812-26ec-4385-873a-05c61b6ef076_769205320": 1.0}}, {"text": "Drip irrigation and mulching can reduce water consumption and promote sustainable avocado farming, with drip irrigation cutting water use by up to 50% and boosting productivity.", "citations": {"c2fce262-24df-4619-bf96-7e34b4b86563_526707270": 1.0}}, {"text": "Implementing sustainable practices, like reducing water and chemical use, can mitigate avocado production's environmental impacts and promote responsible farming.", "citations": {"9f7babf6-335c-4686-b3fe-7602641d29a4_195587657": 1.0}}, {"text": "The global avocado industry has significant environmental, social, and economic implications, requiring a comprehensive approach to address these concerns.", "citations": {"0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_25051651": 1.0}}], "references": ["9f7babf6-335c-4686-b3fe-7602641d29a4_195587657", "063e477f-f6cb-4caf-92f0-2e8f0ac78ac1_269466826", "99536812-26ec-4385-873a-05c61b6ef076_769205320", "0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_25051651", "c4df1771-8297-4414-adac-d7cd6bb376e0_639626865", "695b759e-d787-4a16-9bc5-9f006dc56478_763886478", "c2fce262-24df-4619-bf96-7e34b4b86563_526707270", "0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_55923929"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "encourage", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1054", "run_id": "encourage-crop"}, "responses": [{"text": "The US accounts for nearly half of global avocado demand, with per capita consumption at around 4.2 kg.", "citations": {"0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_25051651": 1.0}}, {"text": "Mexico, particularly Michoac\u00e1n, is the world's largest avocado producer, accounting for 70% of the country's output.", "citations": {"0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_25051651": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado cultivation expansion has led to deforestation, with at least 300 square kilometers of forest being cleared for plantations.", "citations": {"0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_25051651": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado cultivation requires over 1,000 liters of water per kilogram, depleting local water supplies.", "citations": {"18665f57-7b47-4cae-9c9d-5fc30625182f_930516690": 1.0, "9f7babf6-335c-4686-b3fe-7602641d29a4_195587657": 0.5, "e723799f-1810-462b-b84e-a0b5e5a4749d_1052218110": 0.25}}, {"text": "Avocado production is vulnerable to climate change, with Mexico's cultivation potentially declining 31% by 2050.", "citations": {"65e3998a-3ab7-4bb2-b022-ca181d90e86f_222072541": 1.0}}, {"text": "Agroforestry and permaculture systems can benefit avocado production by promoting environmentally friendly farming and mitigating climate change.", "citations": {"0463bbbc-aa29-4e29-ac24-ecb880122424_275801568": 1.0, "08243776-6209-4f58-bf9b-6eba959ce05f_94533784": 0.5, "0e3008fd-5a3a-4ca4-b6c3-40bf8538a121_384136349": 0.25}}, {"text": "Agroforestry and permaculture in avocado production can also increase complexity and cost.", "citations": {"bd68b016-c097-4e82-8666-6b0d76f4f8b8_384434155": 1.0}}, {"text": "Scaling up agroforestry and permaculture in avocado production requires teaching farmers sustainable techniques and providing market and financial support.", "citations": {"08243776-6209-4f58-bf9b-6eba959ce05f_94533784": 1.0, "a22bbc80-d28a-493c-82f4-5b443da86c81_628665012": 0.5}}, {"text": "Governments and companies can promote sustainable avocado production through incentives and supportive laws.", "citations": {"9f7babf6-335c-4686-b3fe-7602641d29a4_195587657": 1.0, "a22bbc80-d28a-493c-82f4-5b443da86c81_628665012": 0.5}}, {"text": "Sustainable avocado farming reduces water and chemical use, and mitigates social impacts like land grabbing and community displacement.", "citations": {"9f7babf6-335c-4686-b3fe-7602641d29a4_195587657": 1.0}}, {"text": "Morocco's avocado production has significant economic benefits, contributing 16 percent to the GDP and $139 million in exports from July 2022 to May 2023.", "citations": {"edc5f60d-13d5-49b0-807a-65a8ddf3ea54_546350791": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado production's environmental costs, such as water usage and deforestation, must be weighed against its economic benefits.", "citations": {"edc5f60d-13d5-49b0-807a-65a8ddf3ea54_546350791": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado production has significant social effects, including displacement and exploitation, that can be addressed through policy interventions.", "citations": {"9f7babf6-335c-4686-b3fe-7602641d29a4_195587657": 1.0}}, {"text": "Companies can prioritize quality, sustainability, and traceability to demonstrate values beyond products.", "citations": {"a22bbc80-d28a-493c-82f4-5b443da86c81_628665012": 1.0}}, {"text": "GLC Cerritos LLC has hired a Sustainability Director to develop a strategy covering governance, human rights, labor, and environmental standards for its 3000-acre avocado farm.", "citations": {"695b759e-d787-4a16-9bc5-9f006dc56478_763886478": 1.0}}, {"text": "The company produces healthy food sustainably, with certifications from Global G.A.P and Rainforest Alliance, and plans to add Fair Trade certification.", "citations": {"695b759e-d787-4a16-9bc5-9f006dc56478_763886478": 1.0}}, {"text": "Policy interventions and sustainable practices can minimize avocado production's environmental and social impacts while promoting economic benefits.", "citations": {"171538f8-76a5-40e7-be21-162696a2cba0_847155343": 1.0}}, {"text": "Certification schemes like Fairtrade or Organic promote sustainable avocado production by emphasizing development and environmental protection.", "citations": {"327b0b71-ada3-4184-ac5c-9feb7b01cea1_145344060": 1.0}}, {"text": "Fairtrade certification improves economic resilience, social wellbeing, and environmental sustainability for farmers.", "citations": {"be539d6d-1b17-4756-ab3f-a6d430f6c214_469398497": 1.0}}, {"text": "Organic certification integrates local culture and environment, promoting local employment and sustainable development.", "citations": {"327b0b71-ada3-4184-ac5c-9feb7b01cea1_145344060": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Participatory Guarantee System (PGS) promotes sustainable development, integrates tribal culture, and creates local jobs.", "citations": {"327b0b71-ada3-4184-ac5c-9feb7b01cea1_739167513": 1.0}}, {"text": "Only 1% of Taiwan's farms have obtained certification.", "citations": {"5230b024-d542-4332-9db3-cf7a3e1038e5_332625603": 1.0}}, {"text": "Some companies, like Cerritos, are securing certifications such as Global G.A.P. and Rainforest Alliance, and pursuing Fair Trade certification.", "citations": {"695b759e-d787-4a16-9bc5-9f006dc56478_763886478": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Rainforest Alliance has certified 1,500 hectares of avocado gardens in Jalisco, Mexico, to promote sustainable production.", "citations": {"c4df1771-8297-4414-adac-d7cd6bb376e0_639626865": 1.0}}, {"text": "Certification schemes can help mitigate environmental concerns by promoting sustainable practices.", "citations": {"695b759e-d787-4a16-9bc5-9f006dc56478_763886478": 1.0}}, {"text": "The current limitations of these schemes include consumer unfamiliarity with certifications like PGS and the farmer-paid certification fee.", "citations": {"327b0b71-ada3-4184-ac5c-9feb7b01cea1_739167513": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado production expansion has caused ecological havoc in countries like Mexico, where deforestation accelerates with a tree cut down every 75 seconds.", "citations": {"c4df1771-8297-4414-adac-d7cd6bb376e0_639626865": 1.0}}, {"text": "Farmers and local authorities are working together with NGOs to promote sustainable avocado production and verify its provenance.", "citations": {"c4df1771-8297-4414-adac-d7cd6bb376e0_639626865": 1.0}}, {"text": "Certification schemes can promote sustainable avocado production, but their limitations and challenges need to be addressed.", "citations": {"327b0b71-ada3-4184-ac5c-9feb7b01cea1_145344060": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado farming causes 300 square kilometers of deforestation.", "citations": {"0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_25051651": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado cultivation is water-intensive.", "citations": {"0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_25051651": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado farming depletes Morocco's water resources.", "citations": {"c0040def-85f9-4219-af40-c61a51ef6006_18395987": 1.0}}, {"text": "A kilogram of avocado requires over 1000 liters of water.", "citations": {"18665f57-7b47-4cae-9c9d-5fc30625182f_930516690": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado farming depletes groundwater.", "citations": {"18665f57-7b47-4cae-9c9d-5fc30625182f_930516690": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado farming contributes to water scarcity in Morocco.", "citations": {"22247f9c-7440-4ae7-b393-f06af488aa34_74740079": 1.0}}, {"text": "Morocco has faced drought for six consecutive years, worsening water scarcity.", "citations": {"22247f9c-7440-4ae7-b393-f06af488aa34_74740079": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado farming in Morocco drains 10 billion liters of water annually, ignoring the dire consequences on water resources.", "citations": {"2409aa08-ac99-4af7-9b03-00162ac09568_658036910": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado production threatens the Kingdom's water and locals.", "citations": {"2409aa08-ac99-4af7-9b03-00162ac09568_658036910": 1.0}}, {"text": "Dams' water reserves are declining due to drought.", "citations": {"2409aa08-ac99-4af7-9b03-00162ac09568_658036910": 1.0}}, {"text": "Rural areas face a water shortage due to avocado farming.", "citations": {"2409aa08-ac99-4af7-9b03-00162ac09568_658036910": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado cultivation leads to deforestation and erosion.", "citations": {"9f7babf6-335c-4686-b3fe-7602641d29a4_195587657": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado production depletes water supplies and causes chemical contamination.", "citations": {"9f7babf6-335c-4686-b3fe-7602641d29a4_195587657": 1.0}}, {"text": "One kilogram of avocado consumes around 1,000 liters of water, causing water scarcity.", "citations": {"9f7babf6-335c-4686-b3fe-7602641d29a4_195587657": 1.0}}, {"text": "In Jalisco, Mexico, a tree is cut down every 75 seconds for avocado farming.", "citations": {"c4df1771-8297-4414-adac-d7cd6bb376e0_639626865": 1.0}}, {"text": "1,100 trees are lost daily in Jalisco due to avocado farming.", "citations": {"c4df1771-8297-4414-adac-d7cd6bb376e0_639626865": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado gardens in Jalisco tripled from 2010 to 2021, causing significant deforestation.", "citations": {"c4df1771-8297-4414-adac-d7cd6bb376e0_639626865": 1.0}}, {"text": "0.51 million hectares of woodland became avocado farms since 2019.", "citations": {"c4df1771-8297-4414-adac-d7cd6bb376e0_639626865": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado farming requires large amounts of water, contributing to water shortages in Mexico.", "citations": {"c4df1771-8297-4414-adac-d7cd6bb376e0_639626865": 1.0}}, {"text": "Mexico faces water shortages due to its growing avocado trees.", "citations": {"c4df1771-8297-4414-adac-d7cd6bb376e0_639626865": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado farming in Morocco consumes 70 liters of water per fruit, threatening water scarcity.", "citations": {"edc5f60d-13d5-49b0-807a-65a8ddf3ea54_546350791": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado production requires 1000 liters of water per kilogram.", "citations": {"edc5f60d-13d5-49b0-807a-65a8ddf3ea54_546350791": 1.0}}, {"text": "Agriculture, largely driven by avocado farming, consumes 87 percent of Morocco's water resources.", "citations": {"edc5f60d-13d5-49b0-807a-65a8ddf3ea54_546350791": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado farming contributes to deforestation.", "citations": {"e723799f-1810-462b-b84e-a0b5e5a4749d_1052218110": 1.0}}, {"text": "Growing one avocado requires 320 litres of water.", "citations": {"e723799f-1810-462b-b84e-a0b5e5a4749d_1052218110": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado farming has a high carbon footprint and affects water resources and the environment.", "citations": {"e723799f-1810-462b-b84e-a0b5e5a4749d_1052218110": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado transportation has a significant environmental impact, with a carbon footprint of nearly 850 grams per fruit.", "citations": {"e723799f-1810-462b-b84e-a0b5e5a4749d_1052218110": 1.0}}, {"text": "The rising demand for avocados has significant social, economic, and environmental implications, highlighting the need for sustainable production practices.", "citations": {"edc5f60d-13d5-49b0-807a-65a8ddf3ea54_546350791": 1.0}}, {"text": "The global avocado market is expected to grow 5.2% per year from 2021 to 2030.", "citations": {"ed28e7a7-da90-4a40-b12e-0760be78ebed_839177627": 1.0}}, {"text": "The US became the world's leader in avocado consumption, with its market more than doubling and imports' economic output increasing 500%.", "citations": {"8ca9c8e9-43b5-47a1-b8c7-47fcb66e4530_31759721": 1.0}}, {"text": "US per capita avocado consumption rose from 3.2 pounds in 2015 to 8.5 pounds in 2019, before declining in 2020.", "citations": {"53ec3f8b-1f33-4db7-b460-fc0533d8e9db_308359623": 1.0}}, {"text": "The US accounted for nearly half of global avocado demand in 2022, with average consumption at 4.2 kg per person.", "citations": {"0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_25051651": 1.0}}, {"text": "US avocado consumption rose 406% per capita from 1990 to 2017.", "citations": {"ed28e7a7-da90-4a40-b12e-0760be78ebed_839177627": 1.0}}, {"text": "Mexico, with most of its production in Michoac\u00e1n, is the world's largest avocado producer, mostly exporting to the US.", "citations": {"0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_25051651": 1.0}}, {"text": "Michoac\u00e1n exports 85% of its avocados to the US, with Mexico expected to have 63% of the global market by 2030.", "citations": {"114d1622-c9c5-4614-b132-9c9189790987_442554566": 1.0}}, {"text": "Global avocado consumption is driven by the healthy eating trend due to their high content of unsaturated fatty acids and dietary fiber.", "citations": {"ed28e7a7-da90-4a40-b12e-0760be78ebed_839177627": 1.0}}, {"text": "Mexico produced 2.33 million metric tons of avocados in the 2021-22 season, amid rising demand.", "citations": {"114d1622-c9c5-4614-b132-9c9189790987_442554566": 1.0}}, {"text": "The increasing demand has raised environmental concerns, including deforestation, with over 300 square kilometers of forest converted to avocado plantations in 2018-2023.", "citations": {"0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_55923929": 1.0}}, {"text": "Climate change may reduce Mexico's avocado land by 59% and the global crop by 14-41% by 2050.", "citations": {"c0a6998e-f6dc-4da7-9421-f8e7e575bd75_992753141": 1.0}}, {"text": "The US avocado market, led by Avocados From Mexico, is worth over $6.1 billion annually.", "citations": {"8ca9c8e9-43b5-47a1-b8c7-47fcb66e4530_31759721": 1.0}}, {"text": "Avocado cultivation has had mixed social effects.", "citations": {}}], "references": ["9f7babf6-335c-4686-b3fe-7602641d29a4_195587657", "0463bbbc-aa29-4e29-ac24-ecb880122424_275801568", "22247f9c-7440-4ae7-b393-f06af488aa34_74740079", "2409aa08-ac99-4af7-9b03-00162ac09568_658036910", "114d1622-c9c5-4614-b132-9c9189790987_442554566", "a22bbc80-d28a-493c-82f4-5b443da86c81_628665012", "18665f57-7b47-4cae-9c9d-5fc30625182f_930516690", "53ec3f8b-1f33-4db7-b460-fc0533d8e9db_308359623", "0e3008fd-5a3a-4ca4-b6c3-40bf8538a121_384136349", "65e3998a-3ab7-4bb2-b022-ca181d90e86f_222072541", "be539d6d-1b17-4756-ab3f-a6d430f6c214_469398497", "327b0b71-ada3-4184-ac5c-9feb7b01cea1_739167513", "bd68b016-c097-4e82-8666-6b0d76f4f8b8_384434155", "08243776-6209-4f58-bf9b-6eba959ce05f_94533784", "0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_55923929", "c0040def-85f9-4219-af40-c61a51ef6006_18395987", "171538f8-76a5-40e7-be21-162696a2cba0_847155343", "c0a6998e-f6dc-4da7-9421-f8e7e575bd75_992753141", "327b0b71-ada3-4184-ac5c-9feb7b01cea1_145344060", "0647188f-9964-4a4f-ae8e-63483708d38d_25051651", "695b759e-d787-4a16-9bc5-9f006dc56478_763886478", "c4df1771-8297-4414-adac-d7cd6bb376e0_639626865", "e723799f-1810-462b-b84e-a0b5e5a4749d_1052218110", "edc5f60d-13d5-49b0-807a-65a8ddf3ea54_546350791", "5230b024-d542-4332-9db3-cf7a3e1038e5_332625603", "8ca9c8e9-43b5-47a1-b8c7-47fcb66e4530_31759721", "ed28e7a7-da90-4a40-b12e-0760be78ebed_839177627"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "encourage", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1055", "run_id": "encourage-crop"}, "responses": [{"text": "Salmon farming commonly uses additives like probiotics, vitamins, and pigments to improve fish growth, health, and quality.", "citations": {"206276b7-7de2-4dab-9189-36c5eec717e8_576973288": 1.0, "de9f2e6e-6769-4635-a399-58552e6eb27d_165935816": 0.5, "dac92579-02ed-4386-a62d-cf5602790d9c_557147700": 0.25}}, {"text": "These additives promote healthy growth, prevent disease, and improve the appearance of salmon.", "citations": {"206276b7-7de2-4dab-9189-36c5eec717e8_576973288": 1.0, "de9f2e6e-6769-4635-a399-58552e6eb27d_165935816": 0.5, "dac92579-02ed-4386-a62d-cf5602790d9c_557147700": 0.25}}, {"text": "The use of additives in salmon farming can have negative health impacts on humans if misused.", "citations": {"ebc22f9a-9095-4f3b-a1e4-f2345c46bd76_389913171": 1.0, "14262a48-23c6-4805-a3f8-3bac32956acc_61620599": 0.5}}, {"text": "Some additives, like emulsifiers, have been linked to negative health impacts, including harm to offspring and disrupted neural connections.", "citations": {"194ab6fb-492b-4134-a822-790a0de32cff_117588944": 1.0}}, {"text": "Eating farmed salmon may increase cancer risk due to high PCB levels.", "citations": {"ebc22f9a-9095-4f3b-a1e4-f2345c46bd76_389913171": 1.0}}, {"text": "Eating farmed salmon more than once a month may increase cancer risk, especially prostate cancer in men.", "citations": {"ebc22f9a-9095-4f3b-a1e4-f2345c46bd76_389913171": 1.0}}, {"text": "Salmon farming additives are regulated by laws in countries like China, which has a strict approval system.", "citations": {"0122fa0a-aafd-4451-8f97-e4a39a9dd88a_574761245": 1.0}}, {"text": "Approved additives are safe, but non-approved or excessive use can have negative health impacts.", "citations": {"0122fa0a-aafd-4451-8f97-e4a39a9dd88a_574761245": 1.0}}, {"text": "The safety of additives in salmon farming is ensured through regulations and testing, but more research is needed to understand potential health impacts.", "citations": {"0122fa0a-aafd-4451-8f97-e4a39a9dd88a_574761245": 1.0}}, {"text": "Countries have varying regulations on additives in salmon farming.", "citations": {"997f84db-2b3b-452f-8a09-199825b51834_283027922": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Aquaculture Act in Norway regulates salmon farming, including additives, with standards varying in other countries.", "citations": {"997f84db-2b3b-452f-8a09-199825b51834_283027922": 1.0}}, {"text": "The use of additives in salmon farming varies by country.", "citations": {"b36d6465-741d-423c-b795-450b5ea78c7f_999369506": 1.0}}, {"text": "Differences in regulations for salmon farming additives between countries can impact farmed salmon's safety and quality.", "citations": {"997f84db-2b3b-452f-8a09-199825b51834_283027922": 1.0}}, {"text": "The use of additives in salmon farming requires careful regulation and monitoring to ensure human and environmental health and safety.", "citations": {"d2f70c93-61ca-4e93-bfb5-e48bb1f59d27_579728869": 1.0}}, {"text": "More research is needed to understand the health impacts of additives in salmon farming and develop effective regulations.", "citations": {"8231ee46-67ef-4047-be0d-ca61de7a9fc4_622700648": 1.0}}, {"text": "Land-based salmon farming is a more humane and environmentally friendly alternative that reduces additives and pollution risks.", "citations": {"8231ee46-67ef-4047-be0d-ca61de7a9fc4_622700648": 1.0}}, {"text": "The use of additives in salmon farming has potential health and environmental impacts.", "citations": {"8231ee46-67ef-4047-be0d-ca61de7a9fc4_622700648": 1.0}}], "references": ["0122fa0a-aafd-4451-8f97-e4a39a9dd88a_574761245", "d2f70c93-61ca-4e93-bfb5-e48bb1f59d27_579728869", "997f84db-2b3b-452f-8a09-199825b51834_283027922", "206276b7-7de2-4dab-9189-36c5eec717e8_576973288", "14262a48-23c6-4805-a3f8-3bac32956acc_61620599", "194ab6fb-492b-4134-a822-790a0de32cff_117588944", "dac92579-02ed-4386-a62d-cf5602790d9c_557147700", "de9f2e6e-6769-4635-a399-58552e6eb27d_165935816", "ebc22f9a-9095-4f3b-a1e4-f2345c46bd76_389913171", "8231ee46-67ef-4047-be0d-ca61de7a9fc4_622700648", "b36d6465-741d-423c-b795-450b5ea78c7f_999369506"]}
{"metadata": {"team_id": "encourage", "task": "multilingual", "topic_id": "1056", "run_id": "encourage-crop"}, "responses": [{"text": "The use of additives in salmon farming is a common practice to enhance the growth, health, and nutritional quality of the fish, with vitamins, minerals, and pigments being some of the most commonly used additives.", "citations": {"39b66508-c08e-45cc-aca1-ebcd84856d91_226266469": 1.0}}, {"text": "Some salmon farms also use uncommon additives such as antibiotics, hormones, and pesticides to prevent disease and parasites, although their use is heavily regulated and often controversial.", "citations": {"8231ee46-67ef-4047-be0d-ca61de7a9fc4_622700648": 1.0}}, {"text": "The purpose of using additives in salmon farming is to promote healthy growth, improve feed efficiency, and enhance the nutritional value of the fish, as well as to prevent disease and reduce mortality rates.", "citations": {"7b6d93af-b92a-4b45-887d-a325a2c58a8a_905125272": 1.0}}, {"text": "However, the use of certain additives has raised health concerns, such as the potential for antibiotic resistance, hormone disruption, and the accumulation of toxic substances in the fish and the environment.", "citations": {"ebc22f9a-9095-4f3b-a1e4-f2345c46bd76_389913171": 1.0}}, {"text": "In countries such as Norway, Scotland, and Canada, where salmon farming is a major industry, there are strict regulations governing the use of additives in salmon farming, including limits on the types and amounts of additives that can be used.", "citations": {"997f84db-2b3b-452f-8a09-199825b51834_283027922": 1.0}}, {"text": "The European Union has established a list of approved additives for use in aquaculture, including vitamins, minerals, and pigments, and has set maximum permissible levels for their use.", "citations": {"997f84db-2b3b-452f-8a09-199825b51834_283027922": 1.0}}, {"text": "In the United States, the Food and Drug Administration (FDA) regulates the use of additives in salmon farming, including approving new additives and monitoring their use to ensure compliance with federal regulations.", "citations": {"997f84db-2b3b-452f-8a09-199825b51834_283027922": 1.0}}, {"text": "Regulations on additives in salmon farming are enforced through a combination of government inspections, self-reporting by farmers, and third-party auditing and certification programs.", "citations": {"adb6b376-1981-4027-92c3-fa738c1690ce_356480643": 1.0}}, {"text": "Non-compliance with regulations on additives in salmon farming can result in serious consequences, including fines, penalties, and even the closure of farms, as well as damage to the environment and human health.", "citations": {"b3821684-191b-441d-9a1c-9253e3c38abd_178094201": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Aquaculture Stewardship Council certifies responsible aquaculture, which includes salmon farming practices, and promotes environmentally responsible seafood.", "citations": {"b8be3139-db85-4a37-97a6-285881298425_473272053": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Marine Stewardship Council certifies sustainable fishing practices, which can indirectly impact the salmon industry.", "citations": {"47170870-0627-4f43-8ab2-685cd60f3628_119418193": 1.0}}, {"text": "Certifications such as the Aquaculture Stewardship Council and the Marine Stewardship Council promote sustainable and responsible farming practices in the salmon industry.", "citations": {"997f84db-2b3b-452f-8a09-199825b51834_283027922": 1.0}}, {"text": "Some companies, such as Mowi, have issued green bonds to fund sustainability projects, including ASC-certified salmon farming projects, which promote sustainable and responsible farming practices.", "citations": {"8b3bb4fb-49d9-45ab-8bce-cd18a8bd3823_785664709": 1.0}}, {"text": "Overall, the use of additives in salmon farming is a complex issue that requires careful regulation and monitoring to ensure the health and safety of both the fish and the humans who consume them.", "citations": {"8231ee46-67ef-4047-be0d-ca61de7a9fc4_622700648": 1.0}}, {"text": "The regulatory framework for salmon farming additives varies by country, with different laws, regulations, and certification schemes in place.", "citations": {"997f84db-2b3b-452f-8a09-199825b51834_283027922": 1.0}}, {"text": "In Norway, the Aquaculture Act regulates salmon farming, and the Aquaculture Stewardship Council has a salmon standard that includes requirements for feed and additives.", "citations": {"997f84db-2b3b-452f-8a09-199825b51834_283027922": 1.0}}, {"text": "The RSPCA also has welfare standards for farmed Atlantic salmon, which include guidelines for the use of additives in feed.", "citations": {"997f84db-2b3b-452f-8a09-199825b51834_283027922": 1.0}}, {"text": "The use of additives in salmon farming can have health concerns, such as the use of antibiotics, which can pollute the environment.", "citations": {"8231ee46-67ef-4047-be0d-ca61de7a9fc4_622700648": 1.0}}, {"text": "Antibiotics in salmon farming can also contribute to the development of antibiotic-resistant bacteria, posing a risk to human health.", "citations": {"14262a48-23c6-4805-a3f8-3bac32956acc_61620599": 1.0}}, {"text": "However, some salmon farms, such as those certified by the Aquaculture Stewardship Council, may use more sustainable and responsible practices, such as integrated pest management and disease prevention.", "citations": {"8b3bb4fb-49d9-45ab-8bce-cd18a8bd3823_785664709": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Best Aquaculture Certification Practice provides international accreditation for responsible aquaculture practices, including the use of additives in feed.", "citations": {"47170870-0627-4f43-8ab2-685cd60f3628_119418193": 1.0}}, {"text": "In countries such as Norway, which is a major producer of farmed salmon, there are regulations governing the use of additives in salmon feed, including strict standards for environmental and health impacts.", "citations": {"8b3bb4fb-49d9-45ab-8bce-cd18a8bd3823_785664709": 1.0}}, {"text": "The European Union has also implemented regulations on the use of additives in animal feed, including aquaculture, to ensure environmental and health safety.", "citations": {"ddfbf100-961c-4347-9841-d2708a758334_1007525405": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Aquaculture Stewardship Council certification ensures that salmon farms meet strict standards for environmental and social responsibility, including the use of sustainable feed additives.", "citations": {"b8be3139-db85-4a37-97a6-285881298425_473272053": 1.0}}, {"text": "The Marine Stewardship Council certification promotes selective fishing gear improvement and responsible fishing practices, which can indirectly impact the salmon industry.", "citations": {"808ce277-5550-4f3f-9855-1e54db0e1d40_755979957": 1.0}}, {"text": "Overall, certifications such as the Aquaculture Stewardship Council and the Marine Stewardship Council play an important role in promoting sustainable and responsible farming practices in the salmon industry, including the use of additives in feed.", "citations": {"997f84db-2b3b-452f-8a09-199825b51834_283027922": 1.0}}], "references": ["adb6b376-1981-4027-92c3-fa738c1690ce_356480643", "8231ee46-67ef-4047-be0d-ca61de7a9fc4_622700648", "b3821684-191b-441d-9a1c-9253e3c38abd_178094201", "7b6d93af-b92a-4b45-887d-a325a2c58a8a_905125272", "14262a48-23c6-4805-a3f8-3bac32956acc_61620599", "47170870-0627-4f43-8ab2-685cd60f3628_119418193", "997f84db-2b3b-452f-8a09-199825b51834_283027922", "b8be3139-db85-4a37-97a6-285881298425_473272053", "8b3bb4fb-49d9-45ab-8bce-cd18a8bd3823_785664709", "808ce277-5550-4f3f-9855-1e54db0e1d40_755979957", "39b66508-c08e-45cc-aca1-ebcd84856d91_226266469", "ddfbf100-961c-4347-9841-d2708a758334_1007525405", "ebc22f9a-9095-4f3b-a1e4-f2345c46bd76_389913171"]}
